      "citation_id": "[CITATION_3]",
      "span_text": "Illustrations of this interoceptive dimension are found, for example, in cardiac timing experiments where afferent heartbeat signals affect decisions, emotional processing, and memory. Three \"psychological\" dimensions refer more directly to the perception of interoceptive signals: interoceptive accuracy, sensibility, and awareness. These dimensions developed from the use of tests of interoceptive sensitivity/ability, such as heartbeatdetection tasks."
